		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Owning a PowerPak, I would definitely be more inclined to buy homebrew games if I could get a ROM to play on it. With a flashcart, spending extra to cover the cost of manufacturing and parts seems kind of silly if you're not a collector, and I would rather just spend the $10 or so the developer would have gotten from the sale and have that go right to them.<br /><br />Personally I don't see anything wrong with just distributing a ROM. Lots of PC games are distributed DRM-free without issues.

		

		</td>
